You have two separate issues:

## 1. `StaticResource` doesn't update at runtime

`StaticResource` resolves **once** at XAML load time. To react to dictionary swaps, use **`DynamicResource`**:

```xml
<!-- ✗ won't update -->
<Label TextColor="{StaticResource PrimaryText}" />

<!-- ✓ updates when the dictionary changes -->
<Label TextColor="{DynamicResource PrimaryText}" />
```

Then swap themes by replacing merged dictionaries at runtime:

```csharp
var mergedDicts = Application.Current.Resources.MergedDictionaries;
mergedDicts.Clear();
mergedDicts.Add(useDark ? new DarkTheme() : new LightTheme());
```

## 2. Android restarts the Activity on `uiMode` change

By default Android **recreates** the Activity when the system dark mode toggles (it's a configuration change). Tell Android your app handles it itself by adding `UiMode` to `ConfigurationChanges` in your `MainActivity`:

```csharp
// Platforms/Android/MainActivity.cs
[Activity(
    Theme = "@style/Maui.SplashTheme",
    ConfigurationChanges = ConfigChanges.ScreenSize
                         | ConfigChanges.Orientation
                         | ConfigChanges.UiMode       // ← add this
                         | ConfigChanges.ScreenLayout
                         | ConfigChanges.SmallestScreenSize
                         | ConfigChanges.Density)]
public class MainActivity : MauiAppCompatActivity { }
```

With `UiMode` handled, the Activity won't restart. You can then detect the change and swap your theme:

```csharp
// override in MainActivity
public override void OnConfigurationChanged(Configuration newConfig)
{
    base.OnConfigurationChanged(newConfig);

    bool isDark = (newConfig.UiMode & UiMode.NightMask) == UiMode.NightYes;
    // swap your ResourceDictionary here
}
```

**TL;DR** — `StaticResource` → `DynamicResource`, and add `ConfigChanges.UiMode` to your `MainActivity` attribute.
